  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Regional Application Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Here at TWIN DISC, we have a proud history of developing and pioneering transmission and propulsion solutions for equipment that fuels the world. Over the years, we've built a strong company that is centered on innovation and employee ingenuity making us an industry leader and respected throughout the markets we serve. As we continue our expansion, we are looking for talented individuals to join our team.</p><p>In this position, you will be the solution provider for our customers by tapping on TWIN DISC’s vast range of power transmission and control offerings.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Primary duties and responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Preferably with experience in designing marine gearboxes</li><li>Research on and conceptualize innovative proposals to meet the ever changing market demands</li><li>Assist the sales team by providing the necessary product knowledge and technical support for supporting our customers and dealers</li><li>Conduct product presentations to both internal and external customers</li><li>Review technical specifications and propose technically sound solutions in compliance with relevant rules and regulations</li><li>Coordinate customer interfacing including technical discussions, installation, commissioning, and field support (as required)</li><li>Work cooperatively with customers, vendors and internal departments to facilitating flow of information as needed to manage project</li><li>Follow all cross functional processes from opportunity to commissioning to keep all aspects of the project moving to meet customer needs</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in industrial and/or marine industries dealing with rotary equipment, mechanical power transmission equipment, internal combustion engine, ECU/TCU control, etc</li><li>Bachelor degree or equivalent in mechanical or marine engineering</li><li>Proficient with CAD software (AutoCAD, Draftsight, Solidworks, etc)</li><li>Willing to travel</li><li>Strong problem-solving and analytical skills</li><li>Able to manage working on multiple projects concurrently</li><li>Open to taking on new challenges</li><li>Proficient in Japanese language (both written and verbal) will be an advantage</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
